    "collapsible_content_JN3rhi": {
      "type": "collapsible-content",
      "blocks": {
        "collapsible_row_UjR4JN": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Can Reviv reverse damage from braces when I completed treatment years ago?",
            "icon": "none",
            "row_content": "<p>I 'believe' it can based on what I have seen.</p><p>Because regardless of the damage you can still resurrect the structure through these biomechanics.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "collapsible_row_tUj3HX": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "What consequences of braces can Reviv help with?",
            "icon": "none",
            "row_content": "<p>I 'believe' Reviv can help with things like facial asymmetry, diminished jawline, neck and back pain, TMJ problems, sleep issues, brain fog, decreased energy, mood swings, and even various health conditions that emerged after orthodontic work. </p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "collapsible_row_6bErhk": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Will using Reviv undo the teeth straightening from my braces?",
            "icon": "none",
            "row_content": "<p>Teeth move during the Reviv process.  But i find that that they generally move in a good way if you are consistent with using it to sleep.</p><p>And so the teeth will move from where your orthodontist put them to where the skull wants them.</p><p>But since the mouthguard is also stretching things out and expanding them, you will be making space for them to align in a more natural way.  At least based on what I have seen.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "collapsible_row_jEbzGk": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "I'm experiencing health issues after Invisalign/clear aligners - will Reviv help with this too?",
            "icon": "none",
            "row_content": "<p>I believe it can.</p><p>In my experience clear aligners like Invisalign cause the same fundamental biomechanical problems as traditional braces - sometimes even more severely. <br/><br/>And so i've seen that Reviv can counteract this in a similar way to how i explained with braces.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
        "collapsible_row_UjR4JN",
